8 Section 4. KRS 344.040 is amended to read as follows:
9 (1) It is an unlawful practice for an employer:
10 (a) To fail or refuse to hire, or to discharge any individual, or otherwise to
11 discriminate against an individual with respect to compensation, terms,
12 conditions, or privileges of employment, because of the individual's race,
13 color, religion, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, age
14 forty (40) and over, because the person is a qualified individual with a
